Bungoma will host more than 3,000 investors in a conference that starts tomorrow until Friday next week.Governor Kenneth Lusaka said the business summit will provide a platform for local and international businesspeople. He said the conference will allow the county to underscore the increasing economic dynamism of counties. It will also address the growing role of Bungoma county as a dynamic player in development, Lusaka said. It will bring a wealth of distinguished opinion leaders and influential investors. The governor said the counties are focussed on wealth creation and Bungoma should not be left behind.